Tropical Storm Katia Is Almost a Hurricane With 70 MPH Winds Over Atlantic

-- B y   L y n n   D o a n
-- 
2011-08-31T20:45:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/tropical-storm-katia-is-almost-a-hurricane-with-70-mph-winds-over-atlantic.html
Tropical Storm Katia is “almost a
hurricane” with maximum sustained winds of 70 miles per hour,
heading west-northwest across the Atlantic Ocean, according to
an advisory issued by the National Hurricane Center at about
4:40 p.m. New York time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lynn Doan in San Francisco at 
 ldoan6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets at 
 dstets@bloomberg.net  